Defendant Jacob C Cholka in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1, 2 and 3 of the amended information.  Court finds the defendant guilty.   The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1: 

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS JAIL. (CONCURRENT TO COUNTS 2 AND 3)

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with: any victims or their residence.
*No contact with the 180 Juvenile Diversion Program or any of its participants;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Mental Health Evaluation and Criminal Thinking Class, at the discretion of the agent.
*Perform 40 hours community service per year for a total of 80 hours total on all 3 counts.
COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 50 DAYS NONWORKING HOURS,  LAST 30 DAYS STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.   
Defendant to report on Friday, November 6, 2015 by 6:00 p.m.  (apply 4 days Credit)

  Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.

